message.content: Enallagma traviatum is a species of damselfly commonly known as the smoky dancer. It is generally small in size and has an elongated body with a narrow waist. Its wings are translucent with thin black veins and span around 25-30mm in length. The male and female have different coloration, with the males being primarily dark blue-grey with black markings and the females mainly brown with green and tan accents. Enallagma traviatum can be found near slow-moving streams, ponds, and lakes in woodland areas. They are active during the summer months and feed on small flying insects.
